"""
=============================================================================
APEX Q — EARNINGS INTELLIGENCE MODULE
=============================================================================

ARCHITECTURE, AND THE ONE DECISION THAT SHAPES ALL OF IT:

  The RELEASE is free and fast. The LIVE TRANSCRIPT is neither.

  At 4:05pm a company files an 8-K, Item 2.02 ("Results of Operations and
  Financial Condition"), with Exhibit 99.1 -- the earnings press release. EPS,
  revenue, guidance, management's prepared quote. It hits EDGAR within minutes
  of the wire. It is public domain and it costs nothing.

  That is also the document that moves the stock. The gap happens at 4:05pm,
  before the call has even started. The call, an hour later, refines the story;
  the release IS the story.

  Real-time streaming transcript feeds (Benzinga, AlphaSense, Quartr, FactSet)
  cost $1,000-10,000/month. They are not wired here because they are not
  affordable here. TranscriptProvider is a pluggable interface: FMP's post-call
  transcript is wired today, and a live provider drops in the day it is paid
  for. There is no fake "LIVE" state. If we do not have the call, the UI says
  we do not have the call.

EVENT STATE MACHINE:

  SCHEDULED -> PRE_BRIEF -> AWAITING_RELEASE -> RELEASE_PARSED
            -> CALL_IN_PROGRESS (only if a live provider exists)
            -> TRANSCRIPT_AVAILABLE -> POST_ANALYZED -> REACTION_LABELED

  Each transition writes a row to earnings_features with the timestamp AT WHICH
  IT WAS KNOWN. Nothing is ever backfilled into an earlier row.

NO FUTURE LEAKAGE -- the rule the whole feature store rests on:

  The pre-earnings brief is written BEFORE the release and never rewritten
  afterwards. The reaction is labeled ONLY from prices dated after the release
  timestamp. A row's `as_of` is the moment the information existed. If you find
  yourself wanting to update a pre-event row with post-event knowledge, you have
  just invented a backtest that will look brilliant and lose money.

CAUSATION, HONESTLY:

  You cannot know WHY a stock moved. You can enumerate the plausible reasons and
  rank them by evidence. Every explanation this module emits is phrased as the
  most likely reading given what is observable -- never as established cause.
=============================================================================
"""

